dcterms:description: The language Dn is defined as the set of strings generated by context-free rules involving matching pairs of parentheses. The dataset is used to investigate the generalization capabilities of self-attention models in learning nested structures.
dcterms:title: D (Dyck languages)

dcterms:description: A derived dataset from the Dyck language, controlling the maximum distance between opening and closing parentheses by discarding elements that exceed a specified distance.
dcterms:title: D[M axDist = d]

dcterms:description: A derived dataset from the Dyck language, focusing on controlling the maximum depth of nesting in the generated strings.
dcterms:title: D[M axDepth = d]
